The solution I have found is the following:

* I installed [django-apptemplates](https://github.com/bittner/django-apptemplates)
* I have created the following file in my templates:

<my-templates>/admin/index.html:
```
{% extends "admin:admin/index.html" %}
{% load i18n admin_static admin_shortcuts_tags %}

{# django-admin-shortcuts changes these blocks #}

{% block breadcrumbs %}
<div class="admin_shortcuts">
    {% admin_shortcuts %}
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block extrastyle %}<style type="text/css">{% admin_shortcuts_css %}</style>
{{ block.super  }}<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="{% static "admin/css/dashboard.css" %}" />
{% endblock %}

{% block extrahead %}{{ block.super  }}{% admin_shortcuts_js %}{% endblock %}

{# end changes #}

```

I recently started using Daphne to learn django-channels.
To keep configuration as simple as possible, I got rid of gunicorn for the moment, thus using Daphne as WSGI for HTTP. 
I'm using Nginx as reverse-proxy and installed the following:

- Django: 2.0.3
- Python 3.6.3
- channels==2.0.2
- channels-redis==2.1.1

Surprisingly, both HTTP and websocket messages seem to work even with no worker running.

What puzzles me is the behaviour of django.urls.reverse():

```
Testing reverse('admin:auth_group_changelist') ...
Expected result: "/admin/auth/group/"
Actual result: "/home/testproject/testproject/admin/auth/group/"
```

Note that the actual result cointains the root of the Django project, instead of a relative address.
If I follow the link, it just works, but this might be a source of problems should the application logic need to parse the url for any reason.
When I run the same code for local development, using the version of runserver managed by Daphne, I obtain the expected result:

```
Testing reverse('admin:auth_group_changelist') ...
Expected result: "/admin/auth/group/"
Actual result: "/admin/auth/group/"
```

This is the view used to run the test:

```
def testpage(request):
    from django.urls import reverse
    from django.http import HttpResponse

    text = """
    Testing reverse('admin:auth_group_changelist') ...<br />
    Expected result: "/admin/auth/group/"<br />
    Actual result: "%s"<br />
""" % reverse('admin:auth_group_changelist')

    return HttpResponse(text)

```
and this is my nginx config file:

```
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name testproject.brainstorm.it;
    location ~ \.(cgi|fcgi|rb)$  { deny all; }
    location ~ /\.ht             { deny all; }

    location /media {
        alias /home/testproject/public/media;
    }

    location /static {
        alias /home/testproject/public/static;
        access_log   off;
        expires modified 1m;
    }

    location / {
            proxy_pass http://unix://home/testproject/run/daphne.sock;
            proxy_http_version 1.1;
            proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
            proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";

            proxy_redirect     off;
            proxy_set_header   Host $host;
            proxy_set_header   X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
            proxy_set_header   X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
            proxy_set_header   X-Forwarded-Host $server_name;
    }

    access_log /home/testproject/logs/access.log;
    error_log /home/testproject/logs/error.log;
}

```
Any suggestion is very welcome

