Version: 0.22.3-113-g807cb42

The export tool tries to insert a dictionary into the DB and SqlAlchemy throws an error `sqlalchemy.exc.ProgrammingError: (psycopg2.ProgrammingError) can't adapt type 'dict'`. The details of the call are too verbose to reproduce, but an example of the offending code is trying to fetch the `hh_member_register.ccs_record.ccs_record.case.index.parent` property from the register household form (XMLNS: `756ec44475658f3f463f8012632def2bc9fbe731`). An example piece of data would be:

```python
'hh_member_register.ccs_record.ccs_record.case.index.parent': {
    '#text': '901376ba-cf61-486a-9bf9-669192a75859',
    '@case_type': 'person',
    '@relationship': 'child',
    'id': '716edbb0-a845-401b-974c-41699a36311b.form.hh_member_register.ccs_record.ccs_record.case.index.parent'
},
```

From the schema export, this is marked as a `string`, as seen in the snippet below:

```json
